The paper deals with optimization of decision sets for energy-efficient MIMO communications, which involves joint adaptation of transmit power and beamforming vectors based on channel feedback. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm combines the approach of Invasive Weed Optimization (IWO) and an Evolutionary Algorithm (EA), which are both techniques commonly used in systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper provides a numerical analysis to illustrate the benefits of the proposed approach, which falls under the domain of machine learning (cs.LG).
